text: Carphochaete wislizeni is a species of Mexican flowering plants in the sunflower family. They are native to Chihuahua, Sonora, and Durango in northern Mexico.Gray, Asa. 1849. Memoirs of the American Academy of Arts and Science, new series 4: 65Turner, B. L. 1997. The Comps of Mexico: A systematic account of the family Asteraceae, vol. 1 – Eupatorieae.
